main event: A ground-visual sighting of one silver, baseball-sized object flying east was reported in Cresco, Iowa in June 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for about one minute.
The report indicates the sighting was 'probable a/c' (probably an aircraft).
The report was filed by military personnel.
The report was distributed to various military commands, including the Air Defense Command and the Air Technical Intelligence Center.
The report includes coded military communication and a date-time group indicating when the report was filed.
photographs: yes, the report indicates photos were taken, but they are not present in the provided information
